	all software component templates of the current release
	* SoftwareRelease.clearInstances() is called in
	ConfDbGui.closeConfiguration() now, ensuring that if a release is
	kept in memory, all instances are properly cleaned up
	* Fix bug regarding the addition of a module to a sequence in the
	GUI
	* change the DB schemas, the data model, and the GUI to allow for
	Sequences in Sequences
	* Keep track of a configuration being changed since the last time
	saved, if yes, prompt the user if he is about to close it without
	saving the changes
	* Remove the strict naming convention for Modules, instead check
	for each Path/Sequence/Instance that the given name doesn't occur
	anywhere else. All restrictions on the parameters of different
	instances of the same type are lifted.
	* Add 'ValidatedNameDialog' to ESSource context menu, to allow for
	the insertion of several instances of the same ESSource

